  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "The crag is located on Åland (Finnish!), which can be reached by ferry from Stockholm, Kapellskär or Grisslehamn.\n\nThe crag is about 25 metres high at its highest point and overhangs by 3–4 metres. Really good, compact granite with thin vertical crack systems, though there is not much to jam.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:skalberget"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Overview",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:skalberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The crag is on Åland (Finnish!), reached by ferry from Stockholm, Kapellskär or Grisslehamn.\n\nThe crag is around 25 metres at its highest and overhangs by 3–4 metres. Really fine, compact granite with thin vertical crack systems, though there is not much to jam.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:skalberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ovrigt": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Other information",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:skalberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The first batch of routes was put up in 1989–91. I (Rikard Hedman) established a good relationship with the landowner, who would always come over to see what was going on. Unfortunately, after a while he was challenged by people who believed there were nesting birds on the crag, so to be on the safe side I removed all the hangers. Most of them have now been replaced thanks to Finnish climbers. I do not think access is an issue any more, but keep a low profile just in case. Most routes are bolted and have abseil chains, but a small rack may be useful if things get too scary.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:skalberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:skalberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "On the road from Godby to Bomarsund, turn towards Sunds kyrka and drive through Brännbolstad. After a while, the crag appears on the right.\n\nThe main wall, from left to right.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-5.6-sol",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:skalberget"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
